BikeSack

Class BooleanInstrument

  • java.lang.Object
    • BikeSack.Instrument
      • BikeSack.BooleanInstrument
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HeadlightInstrument

    public class BooleanInstrument
extends Instrument
    The BooleanInstrument Class extends BikeSack's abstract Instrument This class allows for an Instrument with a Boolean value.

    Useful Methods include:

    setCurrent() Sets the current value to a value of 0 or 1 to represent a boolean value or throw exception if not trying to set value that does not represent boolean values toString() Returns a "On" for value of 1 or "Off" for value of 0
